# apps/web (Next.js)

## Role

Thin renderer only. Each `page.tsx` imports a screen from `@repo/ui` and returns it.

```tsx
import { DashboardScreen } from "@repo/ui/screens/dashboard";

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return <DashboardScreen />;
}
```

## App Router layout

```
app/layout.tsx              # fonts, globals.css, GluestackUIProvider, Providers
app/(auth)/layout.tsx       # redirect if logged in
app/(workspace)/layout.tsx  # AuthGuard + AppShell
lib/providers.tsx           # ApiQueryProvider + NavigationProvider
lib/api-config.ts           # API base URL + token storage
```

## Next.js specifics

- Dev/build **must use webpack**: `next dev --webpack`, `next build --webpack`
- `useSearchParams()` → wrap in `<Suspense>` with a sensible fallback
- Env files: `.env*` gitignored; never commit secrets

## Don't add here

- Screen layouts, forms, tables (belong in `@repo/ui`)
- Gluestack components (belong in `@repo/ui`)
- Duplicate theme/CSS (import `@repo/ui/globals.css` in root layout only)

## Do add here

- API env config (`lib/api-config.ts`)
- React Query provider wiring (`lib/providers.tsx`)

## Local generated files (gitignored)

- `next-env.d.ts`, `nativewind-env.d.ts`
